<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-6126] Reduce rebalance time by not checking if created topics are available</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-6126</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Within &lt;tt&gt;StreamPartitionAssignor#assign&lt;/tt&gt; we create new topics and afterwards wait in an &quot;infinite loop&quot; until topic metadata propagated throughout the cluster. We do this, to make sure topics are available when we start processing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, with this approach we &quot;extend&quot; the time in the rebalance phase and thus are not responsive (no calls to `poll` for liveness check and &lt;tt&gt;KafkaStreams#close&lt;/tt&gt; suffers). Thus, we might want to remove this check and handle potential &quot;topic not found&quot; exceptions in the main thread gracefully.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
